claims:
1.一种并网型风光联合发电系统，包括分别连入电网的风力发电机组、太阳能光伏方阵；其特征在于，还包括：1. A grid-connected wind and wind combined power generation system, including wind power generators and solar photovoltaic arrays respectively connected to the grid; it is characterized in that it also includes:


         检测装置(11)，用于实时检测所述风力发电机组和所述太阳能光伏方阵的输出功率，并转换为功率信号；A detection device (11), used for real-time detection of the output power of the wind power generating set and the solar photovoltaic array, and converting it into a power signal;


         蓄电装置(12)，用于可选择地将所述风力发电机组和所述太阳能光伏方阵产生的电能储存或者释放；An electric storage device (12), used for selectively storing or releasing the electric energy generated by the wind power generating set and the solar photovoltaic array;


         总控装置(13)，用于接收所述功率信号，并控制所述蓄电装置储存或者释放电能；A master control device (13), configured to receive the power signal, and control the storage device to store or release electric energy;


         当所述风力发电机组和所述太阳能光伏方阵产生的输出功率之和大于预定功率的波动范围的最大值时，所述总控装置(13)控制所述蓄电装置(12)储存电能；当所述风力发电机组和所述太阳能光伏方阵产生的输出功率之和小于预定功率的波动范围的最小值时，所述总控装置(13)控制所述蓄电装置(12)释放电能。When the sum of the output power generated by the wind power generating set and the solar photovoltaic array is greater than the maximum value of the predetermined power fluctuation range, the master control device (13) controls the power storage device (12) to store electric energy; When the sum of the output power generated by the wind power generating set and the solar photovoltaic array is less than the minimum value of the predetermined power fluctuation range, the master control device (13) controls the power storage device (12) to release electric energy.

7.一种并网型风光联合发电方法，包括以下步骤：7. A grid-connected wind-wind combined power generation method, comprising the following steps:


         11)检测风力发电机组和太阳能光伏方阵的输出功率；11) Detect the output power of wind power generators and solar photovoltaic arrays;


         12)比较检测到的输出功率之和与预定功率的波动范围的关系；当所述输出功率之和大于预定功率的波动范围的最大值时，转向步骤13)；当所述输出功率之和小于预定功率的波动范围的最小值时，转向步骤14)。12) compare the relationship between the detected output power sum and the predetermined power fluctuation range; when the output power sum is greater than the maximum value of the predetermined power fluctuation range, turn to step 13); when the output power sum is less than When the minimum value of the predetermined power fluctuation range is determined, turn to step 14).


         13)控制所述蓄电装置储存电能，并转向步骤11)；13) Control the electric storage device to store electric energy, and turn to step 11);


         14)所述总控装置控制蓄电装置释放电能，并转向步骤11)。14) The master control device controls the power storage device to release electric energy, and turns to step 11).
